    {
      "id": "27791e50_035b9d8c",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/server-gen/bin/deploy-artifact",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 243,
      "message": "I think you can simplify using param expansion in bash, this I believe these 4 lines below will do it:\n\nproxy_cred=${http_proxy#*//}\nproxy=${proxy_cred##*@}\nhost=${proxy%%:*}\nport=${proxy##*:}\n\nSee example below, works for the 2 url formats (including the credentials one):\n\n[~] \n[~] http_proxy=http://a.proxy.com:8080\n[~] proxy_cred=${http_proxy#*//}\n[~] proxy=${proxy_cred##*@}\n[~] host=${proxy%%:*}\n[~] port=${proxy##*:}\n[~] \n[~] echo \"http_proxy=$http_proxy  proxy=$proxy  host=$host  port=$port\"\nhttp_proxy=http://a.proxy.com:8080  proxy=a.proxy.com:8080  host=a.proxy.com  port=8080\n[~] \n[~] \n[~] http_proxy=http://jhh:abcd@a.proxy.com:8080\n[~] proxy_cred=${http_proxy#*//}\n[~] proxy=${proxy_cred##*@}\n[~] host=${proxy%%:*}\n[~] port=${proxy##*:}\n[~]\n\nIn the final version of the script mark them local, ie:\nlocal proxy_cred proxy host port\n\nYou can also set MVN_PROXY_SETTINGS directly in this function:\n\nMVN_PROXY_SETTINGS=\"-DproxyHost=${host} -DproxyPort=${port}\"\n\nso it is globally visible in this shell",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-29 17:15:08.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
